 D1_US_Situation {
  m_sTitle "I. Situation"
  m_sTextData "Early 1990s. A light armored reconnaissance company is screening the divisions north-eastern flank."\
  "Earlier today, Bravo section of 1st LAR platoon spotted BRDMs moving into the town of Topolniki. Combined with previous intelligence, this suggests a Soviet reconnaissance company is advancing south west from Novaya Petrovka, towards the main force."\
  ""\
  "In response, a Marine Rifle platoon has taken positions in the towns of Sinystok and Vavilovo, making it impossible for the reconnaissance company to bypass friendly forces. Breaking through would require assaulting one of the towns."\
  ""\
  "a. Enemy Forces"\
  ""\
  "Soviet reconnaissance company"\
  "BRDM platoon at Topolniki"\
  "BTR platoon at Novaya Petrovka"\
  ""\
  "b. Friendly Forces"\
  ""\
  "1st + 2nd squad, at Sinystok and Vavilovo. 3rd squad in reserve at 018 115 with Platoon HQ"\
  "LAR Plt, Alpha nearby at 017 114, Bravo NE of Vavilovo"\
  "Mortar from Weapons, further south at 011 099"\
  "Sister platoon, preparing further down the MSR"
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "US"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 D1_USSR_Situation {
  m_sTitle "I. Situation"
  m_sTextData "Early 1990s. You are a Soviet reconnaissance company tasked with locating a US Marine Division, which is known to be somewhere to the south west."\
  "Earlier today, the BRDM platoon briefly spotted a US HMMWV to the south west - factoring in previous intelligence, this suggests the towns of Sinystok and Vavilovo are being defended by at least a platoon."\
  "While pulling back into Topolniki, the platoon also idenfitied a LAV-25 to its south, which might be part of the divisions north-eastern screen."\
  ""\
  "Due to the terrain, bypassing all enemy forces is not possible. To proceed south west, the company will have to assault either Sinystok or Vavilovo and break through."\
  ""\
  "a. Enemy Forces"\
  ""\
  "Motorized USMC Rifle platoon, defending the towns. If attacked, a sister platoon may reinforce it."\
  "The company most likely has mortars as fire support."\
  "Light Armored Reconnaissance platoon, screening its divisions north-eastern flank."\
  ""\
  "b. Friendly Forces"\
  ""\
  "Company HQ (1x BTR-70), located in Novaya Petrovka"\
  "1st platoon (3x BTR-70), together with Coy. HQ"\
  "2nd platoon (4x BRDM-2), in the north east of Topolniki"
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "USSR"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 D0_GL_Overview {
  m_sTitle "Overview"
  m_sTextData "Early 1990s - a Soviet reconnaissance company attempts to break through one of two villages defended by a Marine Rifle platoon, while a LAR platoon screens its approach."\
  ""\
  ""\
  "US Rifle PL must be slotted as he has a special item."\
  "US RTO must be slotted if the mortar is slotted."\
  ""\
  "US LAR and Rifle platoon have slightly different missions, and are commanded by separate players. LAR may coordinate with the infantry PL, but is not under his command (and vice versa)."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
 }
 D6_GL_Notes {
  m_sTitle "Notes"
  m_sTextData "Setup Timer: 5 minutes (USSR)"\
  ""\
  "LAVs have a radio backpack in the trunk in lieu of vehicle radios."\
  ""\
  "End conditions:"\
  "US Victory: 80% USSR casualties OR time limit (60 minutes) reached"\
  "USSR Major Victory: Gain control of either town (>90%, 1m capture timer), then consolidate at least 90% of the company near the AOs south-western edge"\
  "USSR Minor Victory: Same as above, but with over 60% casualties"
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 D2_US_Mission {
  m_sTitle "II. Mission"
  m_sTextData "Rifle and LAR platoon have distinct missions (and commanders)."\
  ""\
  ""\
  "Marine Rifle platoon:"\
  ""\
  "Defend Sinystok and Vavilovo, allocating forces from the reserve squad (1'3) as required."\
  "When needed, the platoon leader (1'6) may call in a sister platoon as QRF to one of the towns."\
  ""\
  ""\
  "Light Armored Reconnaissance:"\
  ""\
  "Continue to screen this sector of the divisions north-eastern flank, with focus on the reconnaissance company currently at Novaya Petrovka."\
  "Support the defense of the towns by coordinating with the Rifle platoon leader, acquiring and sharing intelligence about enemy movements."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "US"
  }
  m_iOrder 2
 }
